---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const howToReach = [
  {
    icon: '✈',
    mode: 'By Air',
    detail: 'Coimbatore International Airport (CJB) is about 15 km from the venue. Pre-book a cab or use Uber/Ola — the ride is around 30–40 minutes.',
  },
  {
    icon: '🚂',
    mode: 'By Train',
    detail: 'Coimbatore Junction is the main railway station, well-connected to Chennai, Bangalore, Mumbai, Hyderabad and most major cities. Auto-rickshaws and cabs are available right outside the station.',
  },
  {
    icon: '🚌',
    mode: 'By Bus',
    detail: 'TNSTC and private luxury bus services (SRS, KSRTC, Parveen) connect Coimbatore with major Tamil Nadu cities and Bangalore. The CMBT bus stand is centrally located and walkable to most hotels.',
  },
];
---

<Layout title="Travel & Stay | Nirmal & Sumi">

  <section class="text-center py-20 px-6">
    <p class="font-sans text-xs tracking-[0.4em] uppercase text-gold mb-4">Getting here</p>
    <h1 class="section-title">Travel & Stay</h1>
    <div class="section-divider max-w-xs mx-auto mt-6">
      <span class="divider-motif">❋</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pb-16">
    <div class="card overflow-hidden p-0">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3916.4!2d77.0!3d11.0!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x0%3A0x0!2sSubhasree+Hall+Ramnagar+Coimbatore!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1"
        width="100%"
        height="280"
        style="border:0; display:block;"
        allowfullscreen=""
        loading="lazy"
        referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"
        title="Subhasree Hall, Coimbatore"
      ></iframe>
      <div class="p-8 text-center">
        <p class="font-sans text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-gold mb-3">Wedding Venue</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-maroon font-light mb-2">Subhasree Hall</h2>
        <p class="font-sans text-brown-light mb-6">Ramnagar, Coimbatore 641 009, Tamil Nadu, India</p>
        <a
          href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Subhasree+Hall+Ramnagar+Coimbatore"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="btn-primary"
        >
          Open in Google Maps ↗
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6"><span class="divider-motif">◆</span></div>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="card bg-maroon bg-opacity-5 border-maroon border-opacity-20 text-center">
      <p class="font-sans text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-gold mb-3">For guests flying in</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-maroon font-light mb-3">Accommodation</h2>
      <p class="font-sans text-sm text-brown-light leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto">
        We're arranging a block of rooms in a nearby service apartment for guests who are flying in. If you need accommodation, please let us know when you RSVP and we'll get you sorted.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6"><span class="divider-motif">◆</span></div>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-maroon text-center font-light mb-10">Getting to Coimbatore</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {howToReach.map(item => (
        <div class="card text-center">
          <p class="text-3xl mb-3">{item.icon}</p>
          <p class="font-serif text-xl text-maroon mb-3">{item.mode}</p>
          <p class="font-sans text-sm text-brown-light leading-relaxed">{item.detail}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-cream-dark py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-maroon text-center font-light mb-10">While You're in Coimbatore</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 font-sans text-sm text-brown-light">

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="font-serif text-maroon text-xl">Getting Around</p>
          <p>
            Uber and Ola work reliably across Coimbatore and are the easiest option for airport and inter-city travel. Auto-rickshaws are plentiful and great for short hops — always agree on a fare before you get in, or insist on the meter. The city isn't walkable in the traditional sense but distances between key areas are short, and most rides cost under ₹150.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="font-serif text-maroon text-xl">Food & Drink</p>
          <p>
            Coimbatore is a paradise for South Indian vegetarian food. Start your mornings with idli and dosa at Annapoorna or Sree Annapoorna — local institutions that have been serving flawless breakfasts for decades. Filter coffee is a religion here; order it as a decoction-milk combo and don't rush it. For something heartier, the Chettinad and Tamil Brahmin thali spots around the city are extraordinary. If you eat meat, the local Kongu-style chicken dishes are worth seeking out.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="font-serif text-maroon text-xl">Weather in September</p>
          <p>
            September sits at the tail end of the south-west monsoon, so expect warm, humid days around 27–32°C with occasional afternoon showers. The rain rarely lasts long and usually cools things down nicely. Pack light, breathable fabrics — cotton and linen work best. Carry a small umbrella or a light shawl, and you'll be perfectly comfortable. Evenings are pleasant, especially outdoors.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <p class="font-serif text-maroon text-xl">What to Explore</p>
          <p>
            If you have a day to spare, Coimbatore punches well above its tourist profile. Marudhamalai Temple on the city's outskirts is a stunning hilltop Murugan shrine worth the climb. The Dhyanalinga meditation centre in Isha is a genuinely serene hour-long experience. Brookefields and Prozone malls are good for casual shopping. And if you want to escape the city, Ooty and Valparai are both within two hours — the drive through tea plantations is worth it on its own.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
